data.title: Woody Guthrie All-star Tribute Concert 1970 — South San Francisco Public Library
data.meta_description: Woody Guthrie All-star Tribute Concert 1970 — The tribute concert at the Hollywood Bowl in 1970 celebrates the work of legendary folk singer and songwriter, Woody Guthrie, and has never been seen before. The star-studded event was a fundraiser for the California Chapter of The Committee to Combat Huntington's Disease, now known as the Hereditary Disease Foundation, as Woody died of Huntington's disease in 1967.
